snippet.textDisplay:
I was checking the reviews of the movie, and this was the first one I saw:


"this movie was a cinematic masterpiece that should be taught in every film class. the cat repeatedly being crushed as a symbol of class oppression was simply revolutionary, and the chemistry of the characters rivals that of the original titanic movie if not surpasses it. the party time rap may just be the single greatest rap of all time. my mother, who was dying of cancer, heard the song, and within minutes she was cured and backflipped out a window.
this movie brought tears to my eyes with how beautiful it truly was. I saw my entire life flash before my eyes as I was struck with the pure awe this movie had to offer.

10/10, would watch again"
